✅task name-Deploy Linux and Windows virtual machine and access them using SSH and RDP

steps-
1. create VM 
choose your-
Subscription: 
Resource Group:
Virtual machine name: MyLinuxVM
Region: Choose closest to you
Image: Select Ubuntu Server 22.04 LT
Size: Standard B1s (for demo/testing)
Authentication type: SSH public key
Username: azureuser
SSH public key source: Generate new key pair

Inbound ports:
Choose SSH (22)

2.Open Terminal / Command Prompt
Use SSH to connect:
bash
ssh azureuser@<your-public-ip>

3.CREATE windows Vm
Inbound ports: Choose RDP (3389)

4.access windows VM using rdp
Click Connect → RDP
Download the .rdp file
Open the .rdp file
Enter your VM username and password
Connect — you’ll enter Windows Server desktop.
